shortDescription.en-US: Developing stronger bond and cohesion among BUET graduates

description.en-US: To establish a common platform for social, cultural and professional activities among the BUET alumni living in Australia for developing stronger bond and cohesion among themselves in order to help and support each other personally and professionally and for providing support to the BUET Alumni and their families who come to Australia for higher studies or professional development or permanent settlement.

We would achieve our mission by pursuing the following objectives that are embedded in the constitution of BUET Alumni.

To establish a common platform for social, cultural and professional activities among the BUET alumni living in Australia. To develop stronger bond and cohesion among the fellow alumni in order to help and support each other personally and professionally. To strengthen connection and fellowship among the BUET alumni residing in Australia by fostering individual growth, well-being, professional development and networking among the BUET Alumni.

BUET Alumni Association Australia (BUETAA) was founded in 2009 to foster stronger bond and cohesion among BUET alumni living in Australia, and to help and support each other personally and professionally.  Engineers and Architects who were involved with the establishment of BUETAA were Dr. Mirza Manirul Hassan, Mahmuda Mamun Runu, Zulhash Bhuyian, Nilufa Akter Keya, Mansurul Haque, Tanveer Ahmed Tomal, Saiful Islam, Hasen Ali, Fazlul Haque, Manjur Rahman, Syed Moyed Hasan and Yunus Rana.

summary.en-US:
21st February, coloured by the blood of our brothers ! We pay immense tribute and respect to the martyrs of 1952 Language Movement !

In 2019, for the first time, under BUETAA banner, BUET Alumni Australia (BUETAA) celebrated International Mother Language Day paying homage to those who laid down their lives for the cause of the Bengali language in 1952, attending the morning March (organised by Ekushe Academy) at Ashfield Park and placed floral wreaths at the Ashfield Park Shahid Minar !

BUETians also participated in the chorus songs -    ....    ....    !

This year, we would continue to participate, along with other associations, BUETians and their friend & family members are cordially invited to participate (March starts sharp 9 am, please consider extra time for car parking in adjacent streets) !

There would be book and food stalls at the venue.
